How to create the Freevo runtime
================================

XXX THIS FILE IS OUT OF DATE! freevo_rt is called freevo_runtimeX now.


Making freevo_rt:
-----------------

Run 'make'. This will create the 'freevo_rt' directory:

> make


Checking out Freevo:
--------------------
Check out the main freevo source for distribution (from freevo/Docs/NOTES):

o Make a .tar.gz file from the tagged version using anonymous export
  cvs -d:pserver:anonymous@cvs.freevo.sourceforge.net:/cvsroot/freevo login
  cvs -z3 -d:pserver:anonymous@cvs.freevo.sourceforge.net:/cvsroot/freevo export \
    -r HEAD freevo

Replace 'HEAD' with a version tag if needed.

(The reason we're not using the version that make_rt is in is that we
 might want to use a different version.)


Make freevo utils:
------------------
Compile runapp, freevo_xwin and vtrelease:

> cd freevo ; make ; cd ..


Copy freevo_rt:
---------------
Copy 'freevo_rt' to the freevo source directory:

> cp -a freevo_rt freevo


Create the final tar-file:
--------------------------

Remove WIP and make_rt?

> mv freevo freevo-<VERSION>
> tar cvzf freevo-<VERSION>.tar.gz freevo-<VERSION>




 